Fixes #25042

I already observed GPU interfaces enabled by default in earlier Safari 18.2 beta versions, see #24939, and I'm still seeing it enabled in the lastest version 18.2 (20620.1.15.1).

Still not seeing it mentioned in release notes, though: https://developer.apple.com/documentation/safari-release-notes/safari-18_2-release-notes. cc @jdatapple and @jensimmons

This PR updates what the collector can automatically test. I know @chrisdavidmills has been adding quite a few GPU sub features which will need to be tested and updated separately for Safari.

items.content_html:
Summary

the support for URLSearchParams class is:

  • v7.0.0 - added as an internal instance (can be accessed via URL.prototype.searchParams)
    • constructor
    • append
    • delete
    • set
    • get
    • getAll
    • has
    • toString
    • @@iterator
  • v7.3.0 - exposed via url module, URL.prototype.searchParams no longer returns an empty list
    • keys
    • values
    • forEach
    • entries
    • constructor support a USVString
  • v7.5.0 - exposed via url module
  • v7.7.0 - support sort() method
  • v7.10.0 - support sort() method
    • constructor support a record or sequence
  • v6.13.0 - backlogged url implement
